Try new task management techniques
 I often feel like I'm trying out a new task management approach.
 	[trade-off between use and exploration].
  Even if you have a system that is working okay now, it is good to try something new
  But on the other hand, during the "give it a try," the cycle that has been habituated and spinning until now is interrupted.
  When you're using System A, you try System B and conclude that System B is not good enough, you don't go back to A.
  It could be argued that going back is the right thing to do.
  	[The idea is, "If what you change is a mistake, don't undo it, but change it further.

